    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nSome of the links between neovim-only highlight groups (also some groups where I'm not sure if they are nvim only) to vim highlight groups in `colors/vim.lua` don't match the links set up in the default colorscheme. I've attached a diff generated with\n\n`print_hl_links.lua`:\n```lua\nfor hl_name, hl in pairs(vim.api.nvim_get_hl(0, {})) do\n  if hl.link ~= nil then\n    print(hl_name .. \" = { link = \" .. hl.link .. \" }\")\n  end\nend\n```\n```bash\ndiff -d \\\n<(nvim --clean -c 'colorscheme vim' -c 'so print_hl_links.lua' -c 'q' --headless 2>&1 | sort) \\\n<(nvim --clean -c 'colorscheme default' -c 'so print_hl_links.lua' -c 'q' --headless 2>&1 | sort)\n```\n[hl_diff.txt](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/25948128/hl_diff.txt)\n\nNote that a bunch of the differences in that diff are inconsequential because some links eventually link to the same hl group in the link chain.\n\nIf this is by design (for example to match vim better) this issue can be closed. If this is an oversight I'm happy to open a PR to fix the discrepancies.\n\nAnother thing to add here is that the default colorscheme effectively defines `@variable` to look the same as `Normal` but not linking to it, while `colors/vim.lua` links `@variable` to `Identifier`. Here's a screenshot that especially shows the visual difference of `@variable` between `default` and the recently added `catppuccin` colorscheme\n\n<img width=\"2560\" height=\"1410\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f76ed373-8a70-4d86-9b34-104a265384da\" />\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nExpected would be that hl group links are set up to match the default colorscheme as a baseline.\n\nHere's another screenshot with catppuccin, but `@lsp.type.variable` is linked to `@variable` (as in the default colorscheme) and `@variable` is linked to `Normal` (what default does without linking).\n\n<img width=\"2560\" height=\"1410\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/90bd9275-23e6-46a3-90b1-b805ac2e92e3\" />",
