            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "The point of `vim.lua` is to match the upstream (Vim) default colorscheme (as it was in Nvim pre-0.11) as closely as possible, primarily for the purpose of not having to update all the (old and functional) tests to the new Nvim colorscheme, and to make Vim's bundled colorschemes work at all. Having it match the new default colorscheme was therefore a non-goal.",
