            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Another thing to add here is that the default colorscheme effectively defines `@variable` to look the same as `Normal` but not linking to it, while `colors/vim.lua` links `@variable` to `Identifier`.\n\nThis is intentional since `@variable` is pretty ubiquitous in many tree-sitter grammars and `Identifier` is one of the few highlight groups in the default color scheme that are actually colored. It was previously linked to `Identifier` hence the behavior in `:colorscheme vim`.",
